    "description": "We at Durian Furniture are looking for an experienced Department Manager based out of Agra. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Durian Furniture:\nDurian Furniture is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage store operations to ensure smooth daily functioning\n• Handle customer queries, complaints, and escalations effectively\n• Assist in recruiting, onboarding, and performance management of staff\n• Build relationships with regular customers to drive loyalty\n• Monitor inventory levels and coordinate replenishment activities\n• Conduct regular stock audits and prevent pilferage\n• Coordinate with the supply chain team for timely stock delivery\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• BPharm / MPharm / PharmD\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Retail Operations\n• Proficiency in Visual Merchandising\n• Proficiency in Category Management\n• Proficiency in POS Systems\n• Proficiency in Inventory Management\n• Proficiency in Team Leadership\n• Proficiency in Sales Techniques\n• Proficiency in E-commerce Integration\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Durian Furniture!",
